Not sure what all the negative reviews are about - I've found this place to be solid.
Popped in here late on a Sunday and found my expectations exceeded.
I ordered crab cakes,a  filet mignon, and potato wedges.
The crab cakes were excellent, the steak was perfectly cooked  (medium) and crusted with peppercorns, the wedges slightly overdone.
My brother ordered crabcakes, a salad with grilled shrimp, and fries.
He had no complaints, and the fries were excellent (I stole more than a few).
The house wine was perfectly chilled and the service good.
The waitress was quite bubbly and perhaps a bit over the top friendly, but overall the service was pleasant.
Surely there's plenty of places to eat at in Vegas, but if I was by here and hungry I would not hesitate to drop in.

